Beijing astronomer Anjiu photographs the Geminid meteor shower in Qinghai on December 13, 2018.
Most meteor showers have their parent bodies as periodic comets, but the Geminids are home to asteroid 3200 Phaethon, an Apollo-type asteroid.
The Geminids are also the second known meteor shower that was not "conceived" by a comet.
Xiu Lipeng, director of the Tianjin Astronomical Society and an expert in astronomical science, said that just like the New Year blockbuster, the Geminid meteor shower generally appears at the end of the year, and the "release schedule" can last from December 4 to 17.
The meteor shower is known for its large and stable flow, and is known as the three major meteor showers in the Northern Hemisphere along with the Quadrant meteor shower and the Perseid meteor shower.
A notable feature of the Geminid meteor shower is that meteoroids are slower, colorful, and have many bolides, which are suitable for both visual and astrophotography beginners.
Tianjin astronomy enthusiast Yang Jing photographed the Geminid meteor shower in Tianjin's Jixian on December 13, 2020.
Astronomical forecasts show that this year's Geminid meteor shower will reach a maximum at about 15:00 on December 14, with a maximum of 150 ZHR (the number of meteors that can be seen per hour when the radiant is directly above the head under ideal observation conditions).
Geminid meteor shower recommended index chart.
"Last year, the 'colorful falling' Geminid meteor shower made a big impression, but this year's Geminid meteor shower will be disturbed by moonlight, and the excitement will be a little reduced.
The 14th is the eleventh day of the 11th lunar month, the moon phase is a convex moon, bright moonlight will interfere with observation, fortunately in the second half of the night the moon will set, at this time the radiant of the Geminids meteor shower will also rise higher.
