How can you observe as many meteors as possible?
"It is not recommended to observe in the city, you can choose a place with a high altitude, low light damage, and a wide view facing the northeast in the suburbs or countryside, and then patiently wait until the moon sets and observe visually."
It should be noted that the Geminid meteor shower has a large flow in all directions, and there is no need to keep staring at the radiant of the Geminid meteor shower when observing.
If you want to shoot a gorgeous 'meteor shower blockbuster', it is best to choose a wide-angle, large-aperture lens, and use high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
